obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_859  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In purified synaptosomes from rat brain, cytohesin-2 interacts with the PDZ domain-containing protein tamalin, which binds mGluR1 at the postsynaptic membrane. The binding of cytohesin-2 to tamalin was identified in a Y2H screen. Cytohesin-2 is enriched in PSD-fractions (Fig. 6a). PSD-95 and mGluR1 were mostly enriched in the PSDIII fraction, whereas tamalin and cytohesin-2 were enriched in the PSDII fraction, indicating a more loosely association with postsynaptic membranes.\n\nAntibody: Rabbit cytohesin-2 antisera were raised against an N-terminal sequence (aa 1-26). The antibody exhibited some (<5%) cross-reactivity with cytohesin-1 and -3. No KO-control. Experimental description: Adult rat whole brains were homogenized and fractionated into cytosols and P1 and P2 membrane fractions..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_859" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

